arcade.agent.module

Interface Module

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Metabolism, MetabolismComplex, MetabolismMedium, MetabolismRandom, MetabolismSimple, Signaling, SignalingComplex, SignalingMedium, SignalingRandom, SignalingSimple

    public interface Module
extends java.io.Serializable
    A Module object is a subcellular steppable.

    Module objects represent subcellular behaviors or mechanisms within a Cell agent, such as metabolism, signaling networks, and angiogenesis. A Module can be implemented with different versions; the specific class can be selected when instantiating the Cell agent.

    Since:
    2.2
    Version:
    2.3.1
